# 🏗️ System Architecture: AI-Based Personalized Learning Platform

> Designed for an **8-hour hackathon** — optimized for speed, simplicity, and impact.

---

## 1. High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Client["🖥️ Frontend (React + Vite)"]
        LP["Landing Page"]
        SD["Student Dashboard"]
        QE["Quiz Engine"]
        PA["Performance Analytics"]
        TD["Teacher Dashboard"]
        LB["Leaderboard"]
    end

    subgraph Server["⚙️ Backend (Node.js + Express)"]
        AUTH["Auth Controller"]
        STUDENT["Student Controller"]
        QUIZ["Quiz Controller"]
        AI["AI Engine Controller"]
        TEACHER["Teacher Controller"]
        GAMIFY["Gamification Controller"]
    end

    subgraph AI_Layer["🤖 AI Recommendation Engine"]
        RULES["Rule-Based Scorer"]
        LLM["Gemini API"]
        ADAPT["Adaptive Difficulty"]
    end

    subgraph DB["🗄️ MongoDB"]
        USERS["users"]
        QUIZZES["quizzes"]
        ATTEMPTS["quiz_attempts"]
        PROGRESS["student_progress"]
        BADGES["badges"]
    end

    Client -->|REST API| Server
    Server --> AI_Layer
    Server --> DB
    AI_Layer -->|Generate Tips| LLM
```

---

## 2. Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)

### ADR-1: Monolith over Microservices
| | |
|---|---|
| **Decision** | Single monolith (Express API + React SPA) |
| **Alternatives** | Microservices, Next.js full-stack |
| **Rationale** | 8-hour timeline, likely solo/small team, no scaling needs yet |
| **Trade-off** | Can't scale independently — acceptable for hackathon |

### ADR-2: MongoDB over PostgreSQL
| | |
|---|---|
| **Decision** | MongoDB (NoSQL) |
| **Alternatives** | PostgreSQL, SQLite |
| **Rationale** | Flexible schema = iterate fast; quiz/progress data is document-shaped |
| **Trade-off** | No ACID transactions — acceptable for this use case |

### ADR-3: Rule-Based + LLM Hybrid over Pure ML
| | |
|---|---|
| **Decision** | Score-based rules for difficulty + Gemini API for content |
| **Alternatives** | Pure ML model, Pure LLM |
| **Rationale** | No training data available; rules are deterministic and fast; LLM handles creative content |
| **Trade-off** | Less "intelligent" than full ML — but ships in 8 hours |

### ADR-4: JWT Auth over OAuth/Session
| | |
|---|---|
| **Decision** | Simple JWT authentication |
| **Alternatives** | OAuth 2.0, Session-based |
| **Rationale** | Fastest to implement; no third-party login needed for MVP |
| **Trade-off** | No social login — can add later |

