### 3.3 AI Recommendation Engine

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["Student takes Quiz"] --> B["Score Recorded"]
    B --> C{"Score Analysis"}
    C -->|"Score < 40%"| D["Recommend: EASIER topics\n+ Revision material"]
    C -->|"40-70%"| E["Recommend: SAME level\n+ Practice quizzes"]
    C -->|"Score > 70%"| F["Recommend: HARDER topics\n+ Advanced material"]
    D --> G["Gemini API generates\npersonalized study tips"]
    E --> G
    F --> G
    G --> H["Show on Dashboard"]
```

**Algorithm (Rule-Based Core):**
```
Input: student.topicScores, quiz.subject, quiz.score

1. Calculate topic_mastery = avg(last 3 scores for topic)
2. IF topic_mastery < 40% → set difficulty = "easy", flag = "weak"
3. IF topic_mastery 40-70% → set difficulty = "medium", flag = "improving"
4. IF topic_mastery > 70% → set difficulty = "hard", flag = "strong"
5. Find quizzes WHERE subject = topic AND difficulty = next_level
6. Call Gemini API: "Generate 3 study tips for a student
   scoring {score}% in {topic}. Keep tips actionable."
7. Return { recommended_quizzes, study_tips, weak_areas, strong_areas }
```

